<A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/02 8:46:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17323.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Potential effect of more potent NPC casters</span><hr size=1> Not potential, its happening. Last night on TP the hardcore AE crowd in seb was having a tough time to keep their group filled. It's really put a huge damper on AOE.<br>
<br>
But another effect of this AI you fail to mention, is that its about killed the game for the casual 1-2 hour a session player. Not everyone is 15 years old with nothing to do but play for 8 hours a night. Those of us married, kids, RL responsibilities that love EQ, but can't dedicate huge amounts of play time, ARE SCREWED. <br>
<br>
I generally get online for an hour or a bit more a couple times a week, then occasionally I set aside time for a bigger raid. Its pretty hard to login and get a group within 10 minutes so and even if I DID get a group in 10 min, that only leaves about an hour to play... so generally I go solo, and have fun doing it.<br>
<br>
Well that shits changed now. People that are thinking these changes &quot;as is&quot; are the best thing to happen to EQ simply are NOT playing the game. I see it in alot of posts here making comments like: &quot;I think this is a really good thing but I'll admit I havent' actually played with the new ai&quot;.<br>
<br>
Something HAS to give here. Either mob nuking has to be lowered, their HP lowered or nerf their ability to melee. Having all of these as innate abilitys has ruined the game.<br>
<br>
