 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/02 11:45:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17323.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Potential effect of more potent NPC casters</span><hr size=1> I'm less concerned with soloing, although I do understand your concerns as a casual player.  I have the TIME to play EQ more, if I want to let my work slide heh...<br>
<br>
It seems possible though that this might rip a dend into AE grouping, although most people don't wear resistance gear unless they are doing raids - now maybe there will be more use for all this.  Certainly my Bard was swapping songs like a madman depending on the pull. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujordzachmar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jord Zachmar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.dzrealms.com/Zlogo_small.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/02 11:55:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17323.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dzrealms.com/Zlogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Potential effect of more potent NPC casters</span><hr size=1> Depends on where you are aeing at.  My group AEs in FG routinely.  I wear my full ToV resist gear while I am there.  Why you ask?  If a shroom roots me on a pull, I am toast.  If a Fungus snares me on a pull, I am toast.  MR above 200 is the only way to go pulling this stuff.<br>
<br>
I have avoided AE in Seb for a while now.  The exp is not that great and the loot would just rot in my bank anyway.  I can only imagine what this has done to Seb AE, Chardok AE, etc.  Bet all those necro mobs make pulling a joy in Chardok. <p><img src = "http://www.dzrealms.com/zachmar_signature.jpg" border = 0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelasto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/02 11:56:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17323.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> I have heard some groups reporting problems, I have heard others saying it hasnt been much of a problem. I think it changes the tactics somewhat is all, and makes a bard a more valuable member than he used to be. Havent ae'd myself yet, so we'll have to see.<br>
<br>
Guildmates that have done seb in conventional groups since the patch havent reported any special problems. 'I got nuked for 685 once' one told me, 'didnt like that much.'. But since she grouped in there for many hours doesnt seem terrible to me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udanenel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danenel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/02 11:57:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17323.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Potential effect of more potent NPC casters</span><hr size=1> One of the best tanks I've ever seen (was guilded with) wrote this after a seb group last night:<br>
