<br>
However, noone that I know that has hunted in Seb post patch has died yet. I wonder how many roots got cast on that tank that got resisted? 100?<br>
<br>
Maybe 1 in 100 roots sticking is too many with 200+ MR, maybe not.<br>
<br>
Maybe, just maybe this could actually alter the way groups have to fight? instead of sitting in a room with one puller, maybe the group will have to move back and forth a bit more, give the puller some backup. That would be a huge change to gameplay I admit heh. And I dont think players could actually cope with such a change honestly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uclaudshadowflare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ClaudShadowflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/02 12:08:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=17323.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> I've got mixed feelings about this change.<br>
<br>
It has made things a hell of a lot more interesting.  Enchanter NPC's casting AE tash then mezzing, Shaman NPC's which are BAD ASS now, and Necro NPC's that almost bring fear to my heart add another degree of challenge.<br>
<br>
Wizard NPC's are overpowering in many circumstances.  A PC wizard without epic can be killed in one nuke by a frog in Seb.  If he's fully buffed with Aego or PotG/Symbol, 2 nukes.  They have melee to match that of their warrior counterparts.  Velketor has been made several degrees harder now that he casts Sunstrike and (possibly) Elnericks.  The strategy I've seen most used was to try and keep Velketor casting so he wouldn't open up with 4x850 melee, but now by casting big mana spells like SS and Elnericks, he runs out of mana much sooner, meaning he opens up with his serious melee much earlier.<br>
<br>
Risk vs. Reward has become unbalanced in several places in this patch.  Sirens' Grotto is much more interesting now, but several times harder with no added benefit.  Several boss fights (Wuoshi casting Winged Death + Moonfire = PAIN) have been upgraded in difficulty, whereas previously they were balanced based on Caster AI at that time.<br>
<br>
Several of these encounters need to be looked at; and in my ever so humble opinion, I would suggest that the most serious of these are wizard NPC's and boss fights; as well as the case of Sirens' Grotto.  VI has said they're on it... so let's hope for the best.  *cringe*<br>
<br>
Claud Shadowflare<br>
